  "texts": [
    "A dataset might be related to an application, but the task could be narrowed down to take inputs that would never realistically occur.",
    "For instance, PUBHEALTH (Kotonya and Toni, 2020) has actionable outputs but lacks realistic task inputs.",
    "The task is to verify a claim based on a professional factchecking report on the same claim that won't be available for an unverified claim post-deployment.",
    "Finally, if a task instance is easy and quick to handle, collaboration with AI is unnecessary: the person already knows what to do, making the reliance irrelevant.",
    "For example, while there might be a use for sentiment classification of laptop reviews (Pontiki et al., 2014), their brief average length of only 15 words allows people to correctly and confidently gauge sentiment without assistance."
  ],
